This paper deals with using deep learning for medical image classification, specifically for detecting diabetic retinopathy. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and sub-sampling to overcome the challenge of labeled training data insufficiency, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions testing the model's accuracy on a previously unseen data subset, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
